title: Dramane Kamaté
text:
Dramane Kamaté (born August 31, 1985 in <a href="Abidjan">Abidjan</a>, <a href="Ivory%20Coast">Ivory Coast</a>) is a professional <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a>er who currently plays for <a href="Andorra%20CF">Andorra CF</a> in the Spanish Third Division Group 17.
Career.
He was signed from <a href="Chengdu%20Blades">Chengdu Blades</a> in 2008 alongside fellow Ivorians <a href="Bamba%20Moussa">Bamba Moussa</a>, <a href="S%C3%A9kou%20Tidiane%20Souare">Sékou Tidiane Souare</a> and <a href="Kourouma%20Mohamed%20Lamine">Kourouma Mohamed Lamine</a>. After one season for <a href="Ferencvarosi%20TC">Ferencvarosi TC</a> of the eastern group of the Hungarian second division, he left in the middle of 2009 to sign for <a href="AS%20Korofina">AS Korofina</a> in <a href="Mali">Mali</a>. After one year in Mali returned to Europe, to sign with Spanish Second Division club <a href="Racing%20Club%20de%20Ferrol">Racing Club de Ferrol</a>. After two years and 12 games, joined to SD Rayo Cantabria.
International.
He also has played for the <a href="Ivory%20Coast%20national%20under-23%20football%20team">Ivory Coast national under-23 football team</a>.
